wikipedia_page.main: Sir Percy Burrell, 4th Baronet DL, JP (10 February 1812 – 19 July 1876) was a British Conservative politician.

response: *Sir Percy Burrell, 4th Baronet; MP for New Shoreham (1862–1876)

The New Shoreham by-election of 1876 was fought on 4 August 1876.  The byelection was fought due to the death of the incumbent Conservative MP, Percy Burrell.  It was won by the Conservative candidate Walter Burrell.
